user.biography: The “Thrill Capital of the World,” theme park boasts world-class roller coasters and 100 rides, games and attractions for the entire family.

node.text: Throw your hands up and high-five if you dare!

node.title: National High Five Day at the Thrill Capital of the World!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Six Flags Magic Mountain on August 14, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Slay this dragon while reaching a height of 170 feet and speeds of 62 mph 🔥🐉 

#ThrillCapitaloftheWorld #TheThrillisCalling #SixFlagsMagicMountain #Tatsu #LosAngeles

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Six Flags Magic Mountain on August 13, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Twisted Colossus: the longest most innovative hybrid coaster in the world! 
Blue or green track? 💙💚🎢
#ThrillCapitaloftheWorld #TheThrillisCalling #SixFlagsMagicMountain #TwistedColossus #FridayFeeling #LosAngeles

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Six Flags Magic Mountain on August 12, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Number 4 on the Coaster Countdown is Full Throttle🎢⏩ with its 3 separate launces and record setting loop and "top-hat". Can you guess the remaining 3 coasters in our countdown?
#ThrillCapitaloftheWorld #TheThrillisCalling #SixFlagsMagicMountain #FullThrottle #LosAngeles

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Six Flags Magic Mountain on August 11, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Number 5 on the coaster countdown is the giant: Goliath💪 Standing tall with a 255 ft. drop. Who can guess coaster #4?

#ThrillCapitaloftheWorld #TheThrillisCalling #SixFlagsMagicMountain #Goliath #LosAngeles

node.text:
